The Gombe State Police Command, on Monday, said the police officer who shot a trailer driver during a stop-and-search operation has been arrested The policeman had during the operation on Monday fired a gunshot at a trailer driver and injured him. In a statement on Monday by SP Obed Mary Malum, Police Public Relations Officer, Gombe State Police Command said the police inspector has been arrested and is under interrogation at state CID. According to the statement, “The Gombe Police Command under the leadership of CP Ishola B. Babaita, wishes to inform the general public over the unfortunate incident that happened today, January 17, 2022, at about 0630hrs at Gombe-Abba Police nipping-point along Dukku-Darazo road while conducting stop and search. ” AP/no. 204365 Inspector Urbanus Ishaku attached to 34 PMF Gombe, shot a trailer driver, one Abdullahi Bello ‘m’ of Bauchi State. “As a result, he sustained injury on his buttock, the victim was rushed to FTH Gombe where he is currently receiving treatment and he is in a stable condition,” she said. According to her, the inspector has been arrested and is under interrogation at state CID. She added that investigation is ongoing and disciplinary action will be taken against the suspect. “The Commissioner of Police wishes to enjoin all the peace-loving citizens of Gombe State to stay calm as the police will not tolerate any act of indiscipline from any police officer. “Any policeman caught in reckless use of his firearm will be dealt with decisively in accordance with the law please,” the statement warned.